title: Grateful Dead Live at Pine Knob Music Theater on 1980-08-27
description: Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Minglewood Blues, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Big Railroad Blues, Feel Like A Stranger China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, CC Rider, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: First Dead Pine Knob Show Great show both sets! The boys covered a lot of great dead tunes. The crowd was really into this show. It started in the afternoon and ended at night. Everybody enjoyed the hot air balloons flying over including the band! The recording is not the best but a good flavor of how tight the band was.Enjoy!

Why 1 review? 81 has many buried treasures and this is one of them... While nothing here will be mistaken for a best ever version, everything is played tight, competently, and with mucho energy. The china-rider is almost a southern rock version of the song- highly enjoyable. As is the rest of the show.

still a great show... ...in spite of all the awesome shows that provide bookends for this one (especially Cleveland 8/26, Philadelphia 8/30)...I like to take an entire tour in its own context, and with that in mind I listened to this recording with rather low expectations, especially since the recording itself is a typical audience tape of an ampitheater, and this with a local crowd to boot (you can tell that the number of Deadheads are outnumbered by those who went to this show just to go to a concert)...the China>Rider alone is worth the price of admission. Once you get past the sound quality, as you will absolutley have to with all of the sud tapes of the Philly 8/30/1980 show, you will really like this show. 4 stars for performance, 2 stars for this (lone) recording.

Great show. One of my first tapes! I admit I am voting with a lot of nostalgia here. In 1980 it wasn't so easy for a 16-year-old to get his hands on new tapes (or any for that matter) - we often needed tapes to trade with others so we could get new tapes. And since we were starting with very few tapes, it was a challenge. But there were always some nice folks along the way!  And that is how I got this tape - from a friend I met that summer. And it was a show that has just happened! So I was psyched and I listened to it over & over (and over). So....no matter what, I thought it was a great show!
